Ha, just my luck...

After the list has been so quiet lately, I leave home for a couple of
days, for a video shoot, and come back to all this :)

I'm mostly a Wedding and Event shooter. I average around 20 weddings a
year. I shoot on a Canon GL1 and this year added a Canon HV10. Cute
little camera, I'm liking it for B-Roll stuff.

On the event stuff, I shoot things like local Ice Figure Skating
clubs, or this weekend I shot a group of kids who do Shakespeare
productions. The lady who started the club originally did it for her
own kids, then 29 years later, she's still doing it!

I recently moved from a smaller town over to Seattle, so that's been
good for business. I've had the luck to run into some good contacts,
so that's always nice.

I'd have to agree with some of the other recent posts, now with the
more stable OS and NLEs, and faster computers, things just work. I've
found myself more times lately, I'll be 3 hours into an edit, and I
realize I've not even saved the project the first time. Used to be,
I'd click something, hit Save. Click something else, Click Save.
click... SAVE... get scared, reboot just in case :)

What scares me the most lately, though, is how cheap hard drive prices
are getting. I just bought a pair of the WD 500 GB SATA drives for
something like $110 each. I needed to move a few projects off the edit
system, so I could finish something else up. Like HOLY CRAP, there's 1
TB sitting there on the shelf... Wow... I only started around 1999 or
so,  I was always under funded and broke, but my first video attempts
were done with a pair of 8.4 GB drives striped on a Promise FastTrack
controller, and a Matrox Rainbow Runner analog capture card... that
never did really work good... I've got an interesting collection of
stuff that never did work, come to think of it :)

